he wheel.";i:3;s:49:"Use a small carpet under your rolling desk chair.";i:4;s:122:"If you still want to keep your wheels on your chair but reduce the friction you can use a small area rug under your chair.";i:5;s:83:"If you have one in a different part of your house use it in your home office setup.";i:6;s:76:"If you dont have an extra area rug something like this would work perfectly.";i:7;s:80:"Rolling office chair casters often leave scratches and marks on hardwood floors.";i:8;s:82:"If you use a rolling office chair on a hardwood floor you are damaging your floor.";i:9;s:128:"So If you want to protect your Hardwood floor from your rolling office chair you may want to use an office chair without wheels.";i:10;s:55:"Chairs without wheels do not harm your floors for sure.";i:11;s:141:"I picked up a couple of IKEA office chairs yesterday and noticed most maybe all models have wheels that only roll when you are sitting on it.";i:12;s:32:"They lock as soon as you get up.";i:13;s:166:"I asked the IKEA associate why and they said it is for safety but for the life of me I cannot think of a single situation where this feature would make a chair safer.";i:14;s:81:"Most office chair buyers stick with the standard wheels that come with the chair.";i:15;s:81:"However the standard nylon chair casters are poorly designed for hardwood floors.";i:16;s:66:"The dual-wheel material is molded from hard plastic usually nylon.";i:17;s:81:"And these hard wheels tend to slide across a surface instead of rolling smoothly.";i:18;s:400:"Install was pretty easy and for a while I was very happy however after about 6 months I noticed that rolling around was getting difficult and when I turned my chair over I discovered that because they are a larger wheel their center of balance is much farther forward than the original casters they applied too much sideways pressure and broke through the wall in the caster socket in the chair base.";i:19;s:137:"If the chair wheels are too hard or small diameter a layer of duct tape around their circumference will lessen their impact on the floor.";i:20;s:127:"Replacing hard plastic or metal wheels w rubber is also an option but will obviously be far more laborcost intensive than tape.";i:21;s:168:"The caster wheels on your chair are an important part of your chair and without them you would not be able to zip and roll around your office as quickly as you need to.";i:22;s:110:"Keeping your caster wheels clean is important and if you dont you will begin to find yourself walking even if.";i:23;s:80:"The good news is changing your office chair wheels is as easy as it can ever be.";i:24;s:201:"With so many people needing office furniture nowadays many manufacturers have created special roller-blade style wheels that are guaranteed to not leave any marks and scratches on any type of flooring.";i:25;s:105:"It can never be overstated how much of an upgrade roller-blade style caster wheels are for office chairs.";i:26;s:86:"If you need new wheels for your office chair these castors are the best wheels around.";i:27;s:145:"Suitable for use on almost any surface the silicone wheels are easy to install and will ensure smoother rolling and reduced marking on the floor.";i:28;s:175:"LEAGOO Fabric Padded Armless Home Office Desk Chair 120 Rocking Mid Back Ergonomic Chair Computer Task Chair Swivel Vanity Chair with No Wheels 41 out of 5 stars 11 19999 199.";i:29;s:83:"UNIQUE SCRATCH FREE DESIGN Stop damaging your floors with low quality chair wheels.";i:30;s:132:"These replacement chair wheels are guaranteed not to scratch or leave marks on any surface including tile carpet and hardwood floor.";i:31;s:88:"UNIVERSAL SIZE Allows these original office chair wheels to be used on almost any chair.";i:32;s:83:"Dont settle for the cheap set that comes on your expensive office chair upgrade to.";i:33;s:89:"The actual wheel of the caster can be made of elastomers nylon steel and other materials.";i:34;s:74:"In some cases the wheel is actually 